His body is two-dimensional and scandalously colorful.
Gravity no longer has power over him, it’s floating near the roof of the room.
He feels a kick.
Behind it, figures of demons with wings, with red flies like blood, deformed, scratching the teeth.
They are chasing him, kicking him with heavy, flaming boots, throwing him against the walls, he feels the pain throughout his body.
Striking and malignant voices resound from the walls and the radio.
He can no longer stand the voices that insult and offend him.
Henning T. pulls out two wires from the stereo, binds them to form a hanging node, and fixes them on a hook on the roof.
