New tools for driving cars
In these days of storms and accidents, not only car workshops win.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered a crash are removed to a workshop, where an expert must evaluate the damages suffered and what will be the cost of repair.
No accident is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated task.
Manually calculate the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including pieces and work, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the latest computer tools would be a matter of minutes.
That’s why almost 100% of experts use this type of systems.
Service providers and solutions for accident assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information supplied to them by manufacturers, then developing it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the American group Solera, is the leading firm; 80% of the valuations are made with its products.
The other firms that compete in the field of taxation tools and processing of industry information are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data supplied by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them supplies the information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be treated does not stop increasing, to the point that in the last five years the same versions, variants and motorizations have been released than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new car comes out on the market, these companies start to work.
It is a very arduous job, because you have to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and enter its price.
In addition, a "smart" graphic image is made of each model where different parts of tourism can be "pinched".
If it is a massive window model, the work may be ready in a week if the process goes very fast.
If it is a minority car, it can take three or four months.At present, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of the cars that are marketed in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models are information about Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile park that runs, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the documentation work and the elaboration of the databases, Audatex has eight centers distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in developing these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data is included, and customers receive updates every two days.
The elaboration of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer varied products.
The most frequent use is focused on repair and maintenance, but according to which countries there are also tools for the management of waste parts or to calculate the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that reports on the value of the used in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support they can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star product AudaPlus, the standard accident assessment solution, intended for experts.
It includes cars, motorcycles and light or heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint bars.
This tool is paid according to use, for each evaluation.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Then each insurance company, which performs thousands of peritations, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the full identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it left the assembly line only by its trunk number.
AudaGlass focuses on the moons of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is an open service to the professional sector on the internet that allows you to ride by vehicles declared total accident.
